			<updated>2026-02-23T03:10:32Z</updated>
			<published>2026-02-23T03:05:29.915081Z</published>
			<ukm:DocumentMainType Value="NorthernIrelandStatutoryRule"/><ukm:Year Value="2026"/><ukm:Number Value="22"/><ukm:ISBN Value="9780338025838"/><ukm:CreationDate Date="2026-02-19"/><ukm:Subject Value="RATES"/>
			
			
			<category term="RATES"/>
			<summary>Article 42(1F) and (1G) of the Rates (Northern Ireland) Order 1977 (“the 1977 Order”) provide that there shall be distinguished in the NAV list as wholly exempt from rates any automatic telling machine which is situated in a rural area during a relevant year ending before such date as is specified by an Order made by the Department of Finance. 1st April 2027 is specified by this Order.</summary>
		</entry><entry>
